reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Much bigger and more versatile than the one our dishwasher came with
reviews.reviewText: We moved recently, and the dishwasher in our new house had a TINY silverware holder. Literally twelve to fifteen pieces of silverware would fill it. This one is a perfect alternative, we haven’t been able to fill it up yet. I would recommend, if you’re looking for a larger silverware container for your dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works better than my original silverware basket
reviews.reviewText: I installed the basket in the Frigidaire (Electrolux) FFCD2413US4A dishwasher in my apartment. The basket is longer and a little bit more narrow than the original but fits well. It works better than the original basket by preventing items from spooning / nesting. It's not flimsy and shows no signs of wear in the two months that I've had it. As others have mentioned, the lid for the center compartment comes off easily; it looks like it has a latch but it's too short to work. This means that if jostled, the lid comes off. However, it doesn't come loose when the dishwasher is running. The manufacturer could improve the basket by making the center lid latch work better and having a way to lower the compartment lids (my Ikea Dragon 6.25" salad forks and 5" teaspoons just hang from the lid slots, not touching the bottom, and I wonder if the 'working' parts of them are 100% clean).
